.SH NAME
fur-cat - Render markdown or image to terminal


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBfur cat  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Render a markdown file or display an image directly in the terminal.

.PP
Markdown files are rendered with syntax highlighting and formatting.
Image files are displayed inline using your terminal's image protocol
(auto-detected: Kitty, iTerm2, WezTerm, Ghostty). Non-PNG images
(WebP, BMP, GIF, JPEG) are converted to PNG for protocol compatibility.

.PP
Supported image formats: PNG, JPG, WebP, BMP, GIF, SVG, ICO

.PP
Use --json for machine-readable output (file path, size, format, content).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for cat

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	output as JSON (file, size, format, content)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB-c\fP, \fB--config\fP=""
	config file path

.PP
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	enable verbose logging

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	disable colors (ascii theme)

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	color theme (light|dark|auto|ascii)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  fur cat README.md
  fur cat diagram.png
  fur cat --json README.md
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBfur(1)\fP


